[assistant] Fixed the Gradle toolchain issue.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - I added `kotlin { jvmToolchain(21) }`, which made Gradle try to locate/provision a separate Java 21 toolchain inside the test project.
[assistant] - The TCK environment already relies on the active `JAVA_HOME`, and toolchain provisioning is not configured there.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Removed `jvmToolchain(21)` from:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle`
[assistant] - Kept the Kotlin source registration so the `.kt` helper under `src/test/java` is still compiled.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated block is now:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```groovy
[assistant] kotlin {
[assistant]     sourceSets {
[assistant]         test {
[assistant]             kotlin.srcDir("src/test/java")
[assistant]         }
[assistant]     }
[assistant] }
[assistant] 
[assistant] compileTestKotlin {
[assistant]     kotlinOptions.jvmTarget = "21"
[assistant] }
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests.
